---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PostList from '../components/PostList.astro';
import Featured from '../components/Featured.astro';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';

const latestPosts = (await getCollection('posts'))
    .sort((a, b) => b.data.pubDate.valueOf() - a.data.pubDate.valueOf())
    .slice(0, 5);
---

<BaseLayout>
    <article class="content">
        <p>In the inflation debates of 2020, economist Adam Tooze argued the need to <em>disaggregate</em>. Every statistic and headline is an aggregate of multiple complex forces. Understanding them requires pulling those forces apart.</p>

        <p>This blog is an effort to actualize this principle, whether the subject is politics, history, culture, programming, books, or something else entirely.</p>
        <!-- <p>Recent posts are below; the full archive lives on the
            <a href="/writing">writing</a> page.</p> -->
    </article>

    <Featured
        title="China and the sea: a story of power, faith and appetite"
        url="https://aeon.co/essays/china-and-the-sea-a-story-of-power-faith-and-appetite"
        source="aeon.co"
    />

    <PostList posts={latestPosts} variant="compact" />
</BaseLayout>
